<h1><em>PLOS Neglected Tropical Diseases</em> Article Type Descriptions</h1>



<a name="debate" id="debate"></a>
<h2>Debate</h2>
<p>Debate articles highlight controversial issues in the field of NTDs.</p>

<a name="expert_commentary" id="expert_commentary"></a>
<h2>Expert Commentary</h2>
<p>In an Expert Commentary, authors discuss the clinical, policy, public-health, or research implications of a freely available research article.</p>

<a name="from_innovation_to_application" id="from_innovation_to_application"></a>
<h2>From Innovation to Application</h2>
<p>From Innovation to Application articles allow authors to discuss new technologies, including drugs, vaccines, and diagnostics.</p>

<a name="historical_profiles_and_perspectives" id="historical_profiles_and_perspectives"></a>
<h2>Historical Profiles and Perspectives</h2>
<p>Historical Profiles and Perspectives look back in history to discuss a notable figure or a control program.</p>

<a name="interview" id="interview"></a>
<h2>Interviews</h2>
<p>Interviews highlight the work of someone who has made a notable contribution to controlling NTDs.</p>

<a name="photo_quiz" id="photo_quiz"></a>
<h2>Photo Quiz</h2>
<p>The Photo Quiz presents a clinical image and brief case discussion followed by questions, learning points, and key references.</p>

<a name="policy_platform" id="policy_platform"></a>
<h2>Policy Platform</h2>
<p>The Policy Platform is for authors to discuss policies that could improve the lives of those at risk of, or affected by, the NTDs.</p>

<a name="review" id="review"></a>
<h2>Review</h2>
<p>Review articles summarize the best available evidence on a topic relevant to the NTD community.</p>

<a name="symposium" id="symposium"></a>
<h2>Symposium</h2>
<p>In Symposium articles, authors discuss a real-world problem, from the clinic, laboratory, or community, and how best it can be tackled.</p>

<a name="viewpoints" id="viewpoints"></a>
<h2>Viewpoints</h2>
<p>Viewpoints are opinion pieces grounded in evidence on topics of broad interest to the journal's readership.</p>

